@Olivia 
  After taking the quiz I found out that "gypsy" was a derogatory word. I grew up thinking that it just referred to free-spirited people that traveled a lot and never settled. I had no idea it referred to Romanian people. I have never heard the history of the word or of Romanian people in general and how that word is offensive to them. 
  I also feel that the terms "chest-feeding" and "birthing parent" is not right. Bearing children and having them is one of the most special parts of being a women, and no matter what gender you identify as, women feed their children from their breasts. There is no other way to "chest-feed" unless you have breasts that produce milk. I think that the term chest-feeding can be offensive to women because it is almost undermining such an amazing thing that women can do that men can't. I believe that people can identify as a man or a women as long as you are happy, but breast-feeding and bearing children is a very special part of being a women that I don't think should be undermined or belittled.

